                antibioticsAndResistance: "An E. coli isolate has MIC = 0.25 mg/L for ciprofloxacin (EUCAST susceptibility breakpoint ≤0.25 mg/L) and MIC = 8 mg/L for ampicillin (breakpoint ≤8 mg/L). Determine the clinical classification (susceptible/resistant) for each antibiotic and recommend which should be used for treatment.",
                transmission:             "A novel respiratory pathogen has R₀ = 4. Calculate the herd immunity threshold. If 40% of the population is already immune from prior infection, calculate the effective reproduction number Rₑ and determine whether epidemic spread will continue.",
