                immuneResponse:           "Propose a vaccine strategy for a pathogen that undergoes rapid antigenic variation (analogous to influenza). Your proposal must: (a) explain why standard vaccine approaches fail for this pathogen; (b) identify a conserved target antigen and justify why it is less susceptible to variation; (c) specify the vaccine type (live attenuated, subunit, mRNA, etc.) and justify the choice; (d) design a clinical trial endpoint that captures both infection and severe disease prevention.",
                antibioticsAndResistance: "Design a hospital antibiotic stewardship programme for a 500-bed secondary care hospital with rising rates of carbapenem-resistant Enterobacteriaceae (CRE). Your programme must: (a) identify the key drivers of resistance in this setting; (b) specify prescribing policies including indications for carbapenem use; (c) propose microbiological surveillance including threshold criteria for escalation; (d) design staff education components; (e) specify how programme effectiveness will be measured over 24 months.",
                transmission:             "Construct an epidemiological response plan for the first 30 days of a novel zoonotic influenza with estimated R₀ = 3 and a 7-day incubation period. Your plan must: (a) calculate the herd immunity threshold; (b) specify containment measures appropriate to the transmission route; (c) identify the data needed to refine the R₀ estimate; (d) model the effect of isolating 50% of cases within 3 days of symptom onset on Rₑ; (e) specify the conditions under which containment would transition to mitigation strategy.",
                vaccines:                 "Develop an mRNA vaccine design strategy for a novel beta-coronavirus with a highly variable surface spike protein. Your strategy must: (a) justify the selection of the receptor-binding domain as the target antigen; (b) explain the molecular mechanism by which the mRNA vaccine generates neutralising antibodies; (c) address the cold chain challenge for deployment in low-income countries; (d) propose a variant-tracking system to monitor whether booster reformulation is needed; (e) design a Phase 3 clinical trial with appropriate endpoints and comparator arms."
